{"title_page": "Sh\u014dmei Yokouchi", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name          = Sh\u014dmei Yokouchi\n| native_name   = {{nobold|\u6a2a\u5185 \u6b63\u660e}}\n| native_name_lang = ja\n| image         = \n| order         = Governor of [[Yamanashi Prefecture]]\n| term_start    = 17 February 2007\n| term_end      = 16 February 2015\n| predecessor   = [[Takahiko Yamamoto]]\n| successor     = [[Hitoshi Goto]]\n| order2         = \n| term_start2    =\n| term_end2      = \n| primeminister2 = \n| predecessor2   = \n| successor2     = \n| birth_date    = {{birth date|1942|3|2|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Nirasaki, Yamanashi|Nirasaki]], Yamanashi, Japan\n| death_date    = {{death date and age|2020|4|21|1942|3|2|df=y}}\n| alma_mater    = [[University of Tokyo]]\n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Sh\u014dmei Yokouchi'''|\u6a2a\u5185 \u6b63\u660e|Yokouchi Sh\u014dmei}}; March 2, 1942 - April 21, 2020) was a Japanese politician. He represented the Yamanashi Prefecture electoral district and later Yamanashi District No. 3 in the [[House of Representatives (Japan)|House of Representatives]] in the national [[Diet of Japan|Diet]] from 1993 until 2002 and was [[governor of Japan|governor]] of [[Yamanashi Prefecture]] from 2007 until 2015. He is a graduate of the University of Tokyo Law Department.\n\n== References ==\n* {{cite web |url=http://www.senkyo.janjan.jp/diet/profile/0068/00068331.html |script-title=ja:\u653f\u6cbb\u5bb6\u60c5\u5831 \u301c\u6a2a\u5185 \u6b63\u660e\u301c |work=[http://www.senkyo.janjan.jp/ \u30b6\uff65\u9078\u6319] |publisher=[[JANJAN]] |accessdate=2007-12-08 |language=Japanese |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090501145627/http://www.senkyo.janjan.jp/diet/profile/0068/00068331.html |archivedate=2009-05-01 |df= }}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-bef|before=}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Governor of [[Yamanashi Prefecture|Yamanashi]]\n|years=2007\u20132015\n}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Hitoshi Goto]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yokouchi, Shomei}}\n[[Category:Members of t